title: Little athletics: high jump
creator_credit: Tony Blane, Australian Little Athletics Union and Shell Company of Australia
brief_description: A young athlete is taught the Fosbury Flop. The run-up, take-off and landing are explained in detail. Includes a series of exercises relevant to high-jump. Gordon Windewyer, an Australian and Commonwealth champion, is seen in action using the Fosbury Flop. Suitable for upper primary and lower secondary levels.
